      "beast_baseline": "but what about terminal neuroplasticity failure? i've read some papers about how long-term chronic stress can actually lead to a permanent state of receptor downregulation where the pathways just... die. if the biological architecture is no longer capable of processing dopamine or serotonin, aren't you just being overly optimistic? i need the actual science, not just \"it'll get better.\" if the neurochemistry is objectively incapable of responding, then isn't the biology itself saying there's no way out?",
